question: Alliumphobia is the irrational fear of which plant?
answer_0: Alliumphobia is the irrational fear of garlic. [1]
answer_1: Alliumphobia is the fear of garlic [1, 3]. People who suffer from this condition can expect to experience a very high amount of anxiety from merely thinking of garlic, let alone actually seeing it in real life. In fact, their anxiety may be so intense that they may even endure a full blown panic attack as a result of it.  Sometimes, the people suffering from Alliumphobia, which is a Specific phobia, try to avoid not only the exact objects (in this case garlic) or situations that trigger it but sometimes in severe cases the thought of those thing all together.  There have been a lot of cases in which an individual has develop a phobia from garlic where they become fearful of experiencing anxiety itself because it would make them feel very uncomfortable in the moment they are in contact with any of those. [1, 3, 2, 4]
answer2: Alliumphobia is the irrational fear of garlic. The term is derived from "Allium," the genus of plants that includes garlic, onions, and other similar vegetables.

question: What type of creature is a canvasback?

Canvasback ducks were once on the verge of extinction due to hunting and development of their habitats, but have made a comeback along with many other waterfowl species [3].
